S2.description:
📅 Date: 17 Dec 2025
🕒 Time: 05:00  (GMT) (Set your reminder!)
💻 Live Stream Duration: 12 Hours

🌟 Welcome to Study Beans’ Study & Productivity Stream! 🌟
🚀 Join me for focused work sessions, motivation, and a supportive community—let’s achieve our goals together! 💪📚✨

⏳ How It Works
🕒 Study Method: We decide our Pomodoro rhythm together! There’s a live poll in the community post where you can vote on the session format. Right now, we're doing gradually decreasing sessions 🥇, but if you’re curious to try other rhythms, cast your vote and help shape the vibe! 🔥
💬 Breaks: Chat, stretch, or try mini-activities like word puzzles, doodling, or meditation! 🎨🧘‍♀️
🌿 Soundtrack: Raw, soothing productivity sounds from my window—birds, rain, and the gentle hum of focus. No music, just nature! 🌧️🐦

🎯 Who is studying?
👩‍🎓 Name: Farzana
🌍 Born and raised in: Tabriz, East Azerbaijan
🗣️ Languages: Azerbaijani, Turkish, English, Persian, a tiny bit of Arabic 
🎓 Background: 3rd-year PhD student at Loughborough University, UK
🔬 Research Focus: Generating Stochastic Earthquake Ground Motions
🎉 Fun Fact: It took me three years to get a 98 in TOEFL (best score: 99)! I took it three times (86 → 94 → 98) 📖🔥




📜 Community Rules
🤝 Be kind—no spam, hate, or off-topic rants. Let’s keep it positive! 💖
📚 Keep chat minimal during work sprints to stay focused.
🌍 Language: Speak any language you like! 
👋 Introduce Yourself: If it’s your first time joining, share your name & country! Let’s celebrate our colorful cultures together! 

🔔 Subscribe and turn on notifications so you never miss a session!
👍 Like, share, and join the chat to stay motivated together!

#StudyWithMe #PhDStudySession #DeepFocus #Pomodoro #LiveStudy #StudyMotivation #LongHourStudy #Productivity #CozyAmbience  #studybeanscommunity

✔️ 컴퓨터 : LG 올인원
✔️ 스피커 : 미디플러스 MI3 II 3인치
✔️ 키보드, 마우스 : 로지텍 K380s, M350s
✔️ 계산기 : fx-9860g3
✔️ 독서대 : 셀프제작(가로 80cm)
✔️ 책상 : e-smart

Hey! I’m Raghav, a student from India (Shimla) preparing for JEE 2026.
Last year, I spent all my time making music and even released 3 tracks on all major streaming platforms (Spotify, Apple Music, etc.) 🎧. But I didn’t study at all.
So this year, I’m dedicating myself fully to studying — while still holding on to my dream of becoming a musician after JEE (whether I crack it or not).

That’s why I’m streaming my daily study routine live — to stay consistent, keep myself accountable, and help others like me stay motivated. 

🕒 Stream Format

Pomodoro 100/10 → 100 minutes focus + 10 minutes break

Meals/Rest → 30 mins for breakfast, lunch, power nap & dinner

Stream Time → Daily from 8:00 AM – 9:00 PM IST (APROX)
Chat Policy → I will only talk during breaks. Chat will be on hold during sessions to maintain focus.

❓ FAQ

Q: What exam are you preparing for?
👉 JEE 2026 (IIT-JEE) as a dropper

Q: Why do you stream your studies?
👉 To stay consistent, accountable, and build a community of learners.

Q: Will you reply in chat?
👉 Only during breaks. During study sessions, chat will be held.

Q: What’s your ultimate dream?
👉 To become a musician after JEE, regardless of the result.

Q: How many hours do you study daily?
👉 Around 10-12 hours using Pomodoro 100/10.

Q: Where are you from?
👉  Shimla (India)

Q: Where do you study from?
👉  Self Study + Compitishun 

Q: Do you stream every day?
👉 Yes, unless there’s an important work that can not to rescheduled.

S25.description:
📩open me:

Hi!
Welcome to another Study with me
Thanks for joining
_________________________

I hope this study video helps you avoid using social media while you study. You will find a quiet and cosy study room ambience in this video when studying at your home. Hopefully, this would get you motivated more for studying. You might hear the rain, birds, typing sounds and the flipping of pages (and cars too, unfortunately) from time to time, and I hope that helps you know that I'm there studying with you!

🔥Key to success - """"BE CONSISTENT""""🔥

___________________________

What are you studying and where are you joining from? I also wonder what type of videos you like, study at the library or study at home? Your opinions are quite important to me; and, if you let me know what type of videos you like to watch, I would be happy. 
_____________________________

✧･ﾟ at the beginning of the study sessions, make sure to:
- turn off anything you're not going to be using to study
- have your materials ready to go
- have drinks/food ready so you don't have to get up to go get necessities
- have a clear idea of what you want to accomplish during the session (i.e., choose a task from your to-do list)


✧･ﾟ during the breaks:
- stop working as soon as the timer hits, even if you're mid-sentence
- make sure to get up, do some simple stretches
- refill anything that needs to get refilled
- talk to friends/update family

✧･ﾟ at the end of this video:
if you want to continue studying, give yourself a longer break and you can the next session video!

you're set to go! ♡
_____________________________
💡Please adjust the volume for each of the background music that comes out.
The ASMR that comes out with 💡 is the sound of burning wood and Rain. 
_____________________________

We have a Chat bot- 🤖
Commands for chat bot- 

!hi - when you join in👋
!start - to start studying
!top - Top Points
!points -  to know your points💯
!complete - when done with the goal

Chat rules:
- Being nice and respectful is mandatory!
- Spamming, harassment, trolling, bullying, repeating and all capital messages are definitely prohibited!
- Please feel encouraged to write in English so no one would feel excluded in the chat :)
- Please check YouTube's Community Guidelines
_____________________________

To those who are starting :
In order to study or do anything for long periods of time you need a strong purpose and you must be willing to endure challenges. If I can do this, think about what you can accomplish. If you're starting out, start from low intervals(10-30 minutes) and gradually increase once you feel you're comfortable. If you feel like quitting, visualize your goals and evaluate your purpose. Learn to accept challenges in your life to become uncommon.

S58.description:
채널 주인은 2026년 14회 행정사 시험을 준비합니다. 일과 공부를 병행하기 때문에 정해진 시간 없이 공부할 때마다 라이브 방송합니다. 궁금하신 것은 이미 합격하신 분들이나 이지행정사 카페에 문의하시면 친절하게 알려드립니다. 

1차 교재 - 시대에듀 행정사 기출문제 
2차 교재 - 이준희 논술약술모음집, 김묘엽 민법계약법 사례단문집, 정진석 행정심판 사례연습, 최의란 사무관리론
공부 방법은 유튜브 '널위한나의경험&행정사', '바른손사' 채널에서 도움을 얻었습니다. 네이버 '이지행정사' 카페는 합격 후기가 도움됩니다. 집중력 향상을 위해 '잠박사' 채널의 '6Hz 세타파+빗소리'를 이어폰으로 듣습니다. 

행정사 포함 목표를 위해 시험 공부하시는 모든 분들 1년만 미쳐서 합격합시다. 
"나의 한계는 뇌가 만든 환상일 뿐이다! 지금 시작해라. 할 수 있다. 하면 된다. 무조건 된다. 될 때까지 해라. 안 되면 되게 해라!!!!"
